###Block: Familiar Abilities
# Ability Name				Unique Key							Category of Ability		Type															Define Stat									Description																																																																									Template						Modify VAR													Spell Res.				Source Page
Natural Armor Bonus			KEY:Familiar ~ Natural Armor Bonus			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Familiar Class Feature.SpecialQuality																DESC:The number noted here is in addition to the familiar's existing natural armor bonus.																																																																			BONUS:VAR|AC_Natural_Armor|(1+MASTERVAR("FamiliarLVL"))/2|TYPE=NaturalArmor.STACK						SOURCEPAGE:p.83
Intelligence Score			KEY:Familiar ~ Intelligence Score			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Familiar Class Feature.SpecialQuality						DEFINESTAT:MINVALUE|INT|5+((1+MASTERVAR("FamiliarLVL"))/2)	DESC:The familiar's Intelligence score.																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.83
Alertness					KEY:Familiar ~ Alertness				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Familiar Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary														DESC:While a familiar is within arm's reach, the master gains the Alertness feat.																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.83
Improved Evasion				KEY:Familiar ~ Improved Evasion			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Familiar Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Defensive												DESC:When subjected to an attack that normally allows a Reflex saving throw for half damage, a familiar takes no damage if it makes a successful saving throw and half damage even if the saving throw fails.																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.83
Share Spells				KEY:Familiar ~ Share Spells				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Familiar Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Special Quality.Extraordinary											DESC:The wizard may cast a spell with a target of "You" on his familiar (as a touch spell) instead of on himself. A wizard may cast spells on his familiar even if the spells do not normally affect creatures of the familiar's type (magical beast).																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.83
Empathic Link				KEY:Familiar ~ Empathic Link				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Familiar Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.Communicate												DESC:The master has an empathic link with his familiar to a 1 mile distance. The master can communicate emphatically with the familiar, but cannot see through its eyes. Because of the link's limited nature, only general emotions can be shared. The master has the same connection to an item or place that his familiar does.																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.83
Deliver Touch Spells			KEY:Familiar ~ Deliver Touch Spells			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Familiar Class Feature.SpecialAttack.Special Attack.Supernatural												DESC:If the master is 3rd level or higher, a familiar can deliver touch spells for him. If the master and the familiar are in contact at the time the master casts a touch spell, he can designate his familiar as the "toucher." The familiar can then deliver the touch spell just as the master would. As usual, if the master casts another spell before the touch is delivered, the touch spell dissipates.																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.83
Speak with Master				KEY:Familiar ~ Speak with Master			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Familiar Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Communicate												DESC:If the master is 5th level or higher, a familiar and the master can communicate verbally as if they were using a common language. Other creatures do not understand the communication without magical help.																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.83
Speak with Animals of Its Kind	KEY:Familiar ~ Speak with Animals of Its Kind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Familiar Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Communicate												DESC:If the master is 7th level or higher, a familiar can communicate with animals of approximately the same kind as itself (including dire varieties): bats with bats, cats with felines, hawks and owls and ravens with birds, lizards and snakes with reptiles, monkeys with other simians, rats with rodents, toads with amphibians, and weasels with ermines and minks. Such communication is limited by the Intelligence of the conversing creatures.																											SOURCEPAGE:p.83
Spell Resistance				KEY:Familiar ~ Spell Resistance			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Familiar Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary														DESC:If the master is 11th level or higher, a familiar gains spell resistance equal to the master's level + 5. To affect the familiar with a spell, another spellcaster must get a result on a caster level check (1d20 + caster level) that equals or exceeds the familiar's spell resistance.																																																SR:mastervar("FamiliarLVL")+5	SOURCEPAGE:p.83
Scry on Familiar				KEY:Familiar ~ Scry on Familiar			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Familiar Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Special Quality.SpellLike												DESC:If the master is 13th level or higher, he may scry on his familiar (as if casting the scrying spell) once per day.																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.83
Speak One Language			KEY:Familiar ~ Speak One Language			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Familiar Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural														DESC:The familiar can speak one language of its master's choice as a supernatural ability.																																																											TEMPLATE:Familiar Speaks One Language																				SOURCEPAGE:p.82

